    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Union Bank of London, | Charing Cross Branch, | London | S.W.</hi></placeName>
                    <date>30 Sept <hi rend="print">187</hi>1</date>
                    <seg type="supplemental">CR Darwin Esq</seg>
                    <salute>Dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I send you herewith £100. in £5. Bank Notes agreeably to your request.<ref target="#foot.f1"/> The numbers of the New South Wales Bonds purchased on your account are as follows:</p> 
<table>
        <row>
            <cell rend="left">N<hi rend="superscript">os</hi></cell>
            <cell rend="left">12260/2</cell>
            <cell rend="left">Series</cell>
            <cell rend="left">A2.</cell>
            <cell rend="left">payable</cell>
            <cell rend="left">1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi> Jan<hi rend="superscript">y</hi> 1892</cell>
        </row>
        <row>
            <cell rend="centre">"</cell>
            <cell rend="left">8827/33</cell>
            <cell rend="centre">"</cell>
            <cell rend="left">L3.</cell>
            <cell rend="centre">"</cell>
            <cell rend="left">1<hi rend="superscript">st</hi>. July 1900</cell>
        </row>
    </table>
 
<p>10 Bonds of £100. each which we have placed with your other Securities in our custody.<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p>
<p>I am Dear Sir | Yours faithfully | Tho Druitt | Manager</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">CD recorded a payment of £100 to himself from his bank account on 29 September 1871 (CD’s Account books–banking account (Down House MS)).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">The purchase of £1000 of New South Wales bonds on 12 September 1871 is recorded in CD’s Investment book (Down House MS).</note>
        </div>        
            
